I feel &lt;a href="http://getpelican.com/"&gt;Pelican&lt;/a&gt; suits me well. I do not use Ruby in my daily work, so I did not
want to go into the hassle of install rbenv and different version of Ruby even
though I liked Jekyll. Hakyll also put in a similar situation where I was not
able to reproduce the setup from one computer to another. Also I am not as
comfortable with Haskell as I am with Python.
Pelican's stability also should help me concentrate on writing the content.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For typesetting mathematics, I am using a &lt;a href="https://github.com/getpelican/pelican-plugins/tree/master/render_math"&gt;plugin&lt;/a&gt; for Pelican that uses &lt;a href="https://www.mathjax.org/"&gt;Mathjax&lt;/a&gt; underneath. Lets see if it works.
Inline math like &lt;span class="math"&gt;\(E=mc^2\)&lt;/span&gt; and displayed math equations like,
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="math"&gt;$$E=mc^2$$&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lets try a Block quote.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Imagination is more important than knowledge&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
